<P>
   YOYO-DOC _ (Los Angeles) Forget Patch Adams. Antelope Valley
Hospital outside of Los Angeles has Dr. Richard Elton, a
68-year-old orthopedic surgeon who dresses as a clown for charity
and entertains patients with a yo-yo he keeps attached to his belt.
To Elton, the funny bone is as important as any other, so he
performs tricks for his patients. By Karen Maeshiro. (Will move in
the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news file.)
