After initial reports of the president's affair, Hyde reacted to
what he clearly saw as a lot of loose talk about impeachment by
saying: ``You don't impeach him for a peccadillo.'' A year later,
angered by what he came to see as Clinton's cavalier attitude
toward the law, Hyde's position hardened considerably. (Carol T.
